    "what_description": "Tribulus terrestris is a perennial herbaceous plant that belongs to the family Zygophyllaceae. It has a prostrate or decumbent growth habit, with a woody base and branched stems that are up to 10 cm long. The leaves are simple, alternate, and pinnate, consisting of 3-5 pairs of leaflets that are 2-5 mm long. The plant produces small, greenish-yellow flowers that are 5-7 mm in diameter, arranged in axillary clusters. The fruit is a capsule, 3-4 mm long, containing 3-4 seeds, and it is a common weed found in dry, disturbed areas.",
